### Integrate Slate Editor into Payload Root Configuration (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/rich-text/slate.mdx

This TypeScript code demonstrates how to pass the `slateEditor` function to the `editor` property of the top-level Payload configuration. This registers the Slate editor for use across the application, although it's a deprecated feature.

```typescript
import { buildConfig } from 'payload'
import { slateEditor } from '@payloadcms/richtext-slate'

export default buildConfig({
  collections: [
    // your collections here
  ],
  // Pass the Slate editor to the root config
  editor: slateEditor({}),
})
```

