### Registering Server Feature in Editor Config

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/rich-text/custom-features.mdx

This TypeScript code snippet demonstrates how to integrate a custom server feature, `MyFeature`, into Payload CMS's rich text editor configuration. It imports the feature and passes it within an array to the `features` option of `lexicalEditor`. This assumes `MyFeature` is defined elsewhere.

```typescript
import { MyFeature } from './myFeature/feature.server';
import { lexicalEditor } from '@payloadcms/richtext-lexical';

//...
 {
    name: 'richText',
    type: 'richText',
    editor: lexicalEditor({
      features: [
        MyFeature(),
      ],
    }),
 },

```

