### Configure Slate Editor in Payload CMS

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/packages/richtext-slate/README.md

This TypeScript code snippet demonstrates how to integrate the Slate Rich Text Editor into a Payload CMS configuration. It imports `buildConfig` and `slateEditor`, then assigns `slateEditor({})` to the `editor` property within the `buildConfig` function. This setup enables Slate as the default rich text editor for your Payload project.

```ts
import { buildConfig } from 'payload'
import { slateEditor } from '@payloadcms/richtext-slate'

export default buildConfig({
  editor: slateEditor({}),
  // ...rest of config
})
```

