### Define a hidden richText field for RenderLexical anchor (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/rich-text/rendering-on-demand.mdx

This example shows how to define a hidden top-level richText field within a Payload collection configuration. This 'render anchor' field can be used to provide a `schemaPath` to `RenderLexical` when the target rich text editor is deeply nested within arrays or blocks, ensuring the server can resolve the correct field schema.

```ts
{
  name: 'onDemandAnchor',
  type: 'richText',
  admin: { hidden: true }
}
```

