### Enable Client-Side Rendering for Custom Components with State

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/migration-guide/overview.mdx

Custom components are now server-rendered by default, preventing direct use of state or hooks. This snippet shows how to add the `'use client'` directive to a component file, explicitly marking it for client-side rendering when state or hooks are required.

```diff
// components/MyClientComponent.tsx
+ 'use client'
import React, { useState } from 'react'

export const MyClientComponent = () => {
  const [state, setState] = useState()

  return (
    <div>
      {state}
    </div>
  )
}
```
